{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Right now is the most exciting time"},{"time":4000,"text":"to see new Indian art."},{"time":6000,"text":"Contemporary artists in India are having a conversation with the world"},{"time":9000,"text":"like never before."},{"time":11000,"text":"I thought it might be interesting, even for the many long-time"},{"time":13000,"text":"collectors here with us at TED, local collectors,"},{"time":16000,"text":"to have an outside view of 10 young Indian artists"},{"time":20000,"text":"I wish everyone at TED to know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22000,"text":"The first is Bharti Kher."},{"time":25000,"text":"The central motif of Bharti's practice"},{"time":27000,"text":"is the ready-made store-bought bindi"},{"time":30000,"text":"that untold millions of Indian women apply to their foreheads,"},{"time":33000,"text":"every day, in an act closely associated with"},{"time":35000,"text":"the institution of marriage."},{"time":38000,"text":"But originally the significance of the bindi"},{"time":40000,"text":"is to symbolize the third eye"},{"time":43000,"text":"between the spiritual world and the religious world."},{"time":46000,"text":"Bharti seeks to liberate this everyday cliche, as she calls it,"},{"time":49000,"text":"by exploding it into something spectacular."},{"time":54000,"text":"She also creates life-size fiberglass sculptures, often of animals,"},{"time":57000,"text":"which she then completely covers in bindis,"},{"time":61000,"text":"often with potent symbolism."},{"time":63000,"text":"She says she first got started with"},{"time":65000,"text":"10 packets of bindis,"},{"time":67000,"text":"and then wondered what she could do with 10 thousand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72000,"text":"Our next artist, Balasubramaniam,"},{"time":74000,"text":"really stands at the crossroads of sculpture, painting and installation,"},{"time":77000,"text":"working wonders with fiberglass."},{"time":80000,"text":"Since Bala himself will be speaking at TED"},{"time":82000,"text":"I won't spend too much time on him here today,"},{"time":84000,"text":"except to say that he really succeeds"},{"time":86000,"text":"at making the invisible visible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92000,"text":"Brooklyn-based Chitra Ganesh"},{"time":94000,"text":"is known for her digital collages,"},{"time":96000,"text":"using Indian comic books called amar chitra kathas"},{"time":100000,"text":"as her primary source material."},{"time":102000,"text":"These comics are a fundamental way"},{"time":104000,"text":"that children, especially in the diaspora,"},{"time":106000,"text":"learn their religious and mythological folk tales."},{"time":110000,"text":"I, for one, was steeped in these."},{"time":112000,"text":"Chitra basically remixes and re-titles"},{"time":115000,"text":"these iconic images"},{"time":117000,"text":"to tease out some of the sexual and gender politics"},{"time":121000,"text":"embedded in these deeply influential comics."},{"time":123000,"text":"And she uses this vocabulary in her installation work as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129000,"text":"Jitish Kallat successfully practices across photography,"},{"time":133000,"text":"sculpture, painting and installation."},{"time":136000,"text":"As you can see, he's heavily influenced"},{"time":138000,"text":"by graffiti and street art,"},{"time":140000,"text":"and his home city of Mumbai is an ever-present element in his work."},{"time":143000,"text":"He really captures that sense of density"},{"time":146000,"text":"and energy which really characterizes modern urban Bombay."},{"time":151000,"text":"He also creates phantasmagoric sculptures"},{"time":153000,"text":"made of bones from cast resin."},{"time":156000,"text":"Here he envisions the carcass"},{"time":158000,"text":"of an autorickshaw he once witnessed burning in a riot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162000,"text":"This next artist, N.S. Harsha,"},{"time":164000,"text":"actually has a studio right here in Mysore."},{"time":167000,"text":"He's putting a contemporary spin on the miniature tradition."},{"time":170000,"text":"He creates these fine, delicate images"},{"time":173000,"text":"which he then repeats on a massive scale."},{"time":177000,"text":"He uses scale to more and more spectacular effect,"},{"time":180000,"text":"whether on the roof of a temple in Singapore,"},{"time":184000,"text":"or in his increasingly ambitious installation work,"},{"time":186000,"text":"here with 192 functioning sewing machines,"},{"time":189000,"text":"fabricating the flags of every member of the United Nations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195000,"text":"Mumbai-based Dhruvi Acharya"},{"time":197000,"text":"builds on her love of comic books and street art"},{"time":199000,"text":"to comment on the roles and expectations"},{"time":201000,"text":"of modern Indian women."},{"time":204000,"text":"She too mines the rich source material of amar chitra kathas,"},{"time":207000,"text":"but in a very different way than Chitra Ganesh."},{"time":210000,"text":"In this particular work, she actually strips out the images"},{"time":213000,"text":"and leaves the actual text"},{"time":215000,"text":"to reveal something previously unseen, and provocative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"Raqib Shaw is Kolkata-born,"},{"time":223000,"text":"Kashmir-raised,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and London-trained."},{"time":227000,"text":"He too is reinventing the miniature tradition."},{"time":230000,"text":"He creates these opulent tableaus inspired by Hieronymus Bosch,"},{"time":234000,"text":"but also by the Kashmiri textiles of his youth."},{"time":237000,"text":"He actually applies metallic industrial paints to his work"},{"time":241000,"text":"using porcupine quills to get this rich detailed effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"I'm kind of cheating with this next artist"},{"time":250000,"text":"since Raqs Media Collective are really"},{"time":252000,"text":"three artists working together."},{"time":254000,"text":"Raqs are probably the foremost practitioners"},{"time":256000,"text":"of multimedia art in India today,"},{"time":258000,"text":"working across photography, video and installation."},{"time":262000,"text":"They frequently explore themes of globalization and urbanization,"},{"time":265000,"text":"and their home of Delhi is a frequent element in their work."},{"time":268000,"text":"Here, they invite the viewer to analyze a crime"},{"time":272000,"text":"looking at evidence and clues embedded"},{"time":274000,"text":"in five narratives on these five different screens,"},{"time":276000,"text":"in which the city itself may have been the culprit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"This next artist is probably the alpha male"},{"time":283000,"text":"of contemporary Indian art, Subodh Gupta."},{"time":286000,"text":"He was first known for creating giant photo-realistic canvases,"},{"time":290000,"text":"paintings of everyday objects,"},{"time":292000,"text":"the stainless steel kitchen vessels and tiffin containers"},{"time":295000,"text":"known to every Indian."},{"time":298000,"text":"He celebrates these local and mundane objects globally,"},{"time":301000,"text":"and on a grander and grander scale,"},{"time":303000,"text":"by incorporating them into ever more colossal"},{"time":306000,"text":"sculptures and installations."},{"time":312000,"text":"And finally number 10, last and certainly not least,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":315000,"text":"Ranjani Shettar,"},{"time":317000,"text":"who lives and works here in the state of Karnataka,"},{"time":319000,"text":"creates ethereal sculptures and installations"},{"time":321000,"text":"that really marry the organic to the industrial,"},{"time":324000,"text":"and brings, like Subodh, the local global."},{"time":327000,"text":"These are actually wires wrapped in muslin"},{"time":330000,"text":"and steeped in vegetable dye."},{"time":332000,"text":"And she arranges them so that the viewer"},{"time":334000,"text":"actually has to navigate through the space,"},{"time":336000,"text":"and interact with the objects."},{"time":338000,"text":"And light and shadow are a very important part of her work."},{"time":341000,"text":"She also explores themes of consumerism,"},{"time":343000,"text":"and the environment, such as in this work,"},{"time":345000,"text":"where these basket-like objects look organic and woven,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and are woven,"},{"time":350000,"text":"but with the strips of steel, salvaged from cars"},{"time":353000,"text":"that she found in a Bangalore junkyard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"10 artists, six minutes, I know that was a lot to take in."},{"time":361000,"text":"But I can only hope I've whet your appetite"},{"time":363000,"text":"to go out and see and learn more"},{"time":365000,"text":"about the amazing things that are happening in art in India today."},{"time":368000,"text":"Thank you very much for looking and listening."},{"time":371000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}